{"type":"message","id":"3108b805","parentId":"d326b6ed","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:10:42.112Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"write_1771168241831_378","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 203 bytes to .github/dependabot.yml"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771168242110}}
{"type":"message","id":"e7d29508","parentId":"3108b805","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:10:42.117Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"write_1771168241947_379","toolName":"write","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Successfully wrote 1003 bytes to .github/workflows/docker-publish.yml"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771168242115}}
{"type":"message","id":"5a6d5a24","parentId":"e7d29508","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:10:42.124Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"read_1771168242076_380","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# 🧠 DMarket Telegram Bot: Dual Brain Architecture (2026)\r\n\r\n<!-- Badges: Project Info -->\r\n[![Build Status](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/ci.yml?branch=main&label=Build&logo=github)](https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/actions/workflows/ci.yml)\r\n[![Python Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.10%2B-blue?logo=python&logoColor=white)](https://www.python.org/)\r\n[![License](https://img.shields.io/github/license/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot?color=green)](LICENSE)\r\n[![Maintained](https://img.shields.io/badge/Maintained%3F-Yes%20(2026)-brightgreen.svg)](https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot/graphs/commit-activity)\r\n[![Dual Brain](https://img.shields.io/badge/Architecture-Dual%20Brain-purple?logo=openai)](https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot)\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n\r\n## 🌟 Key Features (2026 Edition)\r\n\r\n### 🧠 Dual Brain System\r\nThe system dynamically switches cognitive models based on task complexity:\r\n*   **Gemini 3 Flash:** Handles high-speed, low-latency tasks like market scanning and basic pattern recognition.\r\n*   **Gemini 3 Pro:** Engages for complex strategic decisions, risk assessment, and code self-optimization.\r\n\r\n### 🛡️ Advanced Resilience\r\nBuilt for stability in volatile market conditions:\r\n*   **Circuit Breaker:** Automatically detects API failures and pauses requests to prevent bans.\r\n*   **Bulkhead Pattern:** Isolates critical components so a failure in one module (e.g., price history) doesn't crash the trading engine.\r\n\r\n### ⚡ Scalable Architecture\r\n*   **Fully Asynchronous Engine:** Powered by the new `integrated_arbitrage_scanner`, capable of processing thousands of market updates per second without blocking.\r\n*   **Event-Driven Design:** Decoupled components communicate via an internal event bus for maximum flexibility.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## 📋 Project Overview\r\n\r\n| Metric               | Value                      |\r\n| -------------------- | -------------------------- |\r\n| **Architecture**     | Dual Brain (Logic + AI)    |\r\n| **Python**           | 3.11+                      |\r\n| **Testing**          | Comprehensive CI/CD        |\r\n| **License**          | MIT                        |\r\n\r\n## 🎯 Core Capabilities\r\n\r\n- **Multi-Game Arbitrage:** CS2, Dota 2, TF2, Rust.\r\n- **Advanced Target System:** Smart buy orders with auto-adjustment.\r\n- **Real-Time Monitoring:** WebSocket-based price tracking.\r\n- **AI-Powered:** Market sentiment analysis and self-healing capabilities.\r\n- **Secure:** Encrypted credentials and robust error handling.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## 🆕 Modular Skills (2026 Standard)\r\n\r\nThe project utilizes a modular skills architecture for rapid capability expansion:\r\n\r\n| Skill | Category | Description | Status |\r\n|-------|-----------|----------|--------|\r\n| **AI Arbitrage Predictor** | Data & AI | ML-based opportunity forecasting | ✅ Active |\r\n| **NLP Command Handler** | Interaction | Natural language control | ✅ Active |\r\n| **Portfolio Risk AI** | Finance | Deep portfolio analysis | ✅ Active |\r\n| **SkillsMP Integration** | DevOps | Seamless extension marketplace | ✅ Active |\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## 🚀 Quick Start\r\n\r\n### 1. Environment Setup\r\n```bash\r\ngit clone https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot.git\r\ncd DMarket-Telegram-Bot\r\npython -m venv .venv\r\nsource .venv/bin/activate  # Windows: .venv\\Scripts\\activate\r\npip install -r requirements.txt\r\n```\r\n\r\n### 2. Configuration\r\nCopy `.env.example` to `.env` and configure your API keys:\r\n```bash\r\ncp .env.example .env\r\n```\r\n*Required:* `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`, `DMARKET_PUBLIC_KEY`, `DMARKET_SECRET_KEY`.\r\n\r\n### 3. Launch\r\n```bash\r\npython -m src.main\r\n```\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## 🛠️ DevOps & Infrastructure\r\n\r\nThis repository adheres to modern 2026 standards:\r\n*   **CI/CD:** Automated testing and linting via GitHub Actions.\r\n*   **Docker:** Full containerization support.\r\n*   **Security:** Automated dependency scanning and secret detection.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n## 🤝 Contributing\r\n\r\nWe welcome contributions! Please follow the `CONTRIBUTING.md` guidelines.\r\n\r\n1.  Fork the repository.\r\n2.  Create a feature branch.\r\n3.  Commit your changes.\r\n4.  Push to the branch.\r\n5.  Open a Pull Request.\r\n\r\n---\r\n\r\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1771168242122}}
{"type":"message","id":"90a3297d","parentId":"5a6d5a24","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:10:57.982Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Refining the Documentation**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI've just finished the core CI/CD pipeline and related Docker publishing setup. I've also reviewed the current README. Now, I'm focusing on the README updates. The next step is to add badges for CI status and the MIT license, using Shields.io.\n\n\n**Revising the Badges**\n\n\\n\\n\n\nI've updated the README with specific badges, adjusting links to reflect the new workflows. The CI status now points correctly to `ci-cd.yml`. I’ve also added the “How to Contribute” section, linking to the knowledge base. Next up, I need to execute the git commands.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"write_1771168257840_381","name":"write","arguments":{"file_path":"README.md","content":"# 🧠 DMarket Telegram Bot: Dual Brain Architecture (2026)\n\n<!-- Badges: Project Info -->\n[![CI Status](https://img.shields.io/github/actions/workflow/status/${{ github.repository }}/ci-cd.yml?label=CI&logo=github)](https://github.com/${{ github.repository }}/actions/workflows/ci-cd.yml)\n[![Python Version](https://img.shields.io/badge/python-3.11%20%7C%203.14--dev-blue?logo=python&logoColor=white)](https://www.python.org/)\n[![License: MIT](https://img.shields.io/badge/License-MIT-yellow.svg)](https://opensource.org/licenses/MIT)\n\n---\n\n## 🌟 Key Features (2026 Edition)\n\n### 🧠 Dual Brain System\nThe system dynamically switches cognitive models based on task complexity:\n*   **Gemini 3 Flash:** Handles high-speed, low-latency tasks like market scanning and basic pattern recognition.\n*   **Gemini 3 Pro:** Engages for complex strategic decisions, risk assessment, and code self-optimization.\n\n### 🛡️ Advanced Resilience\nBuilt for stability in volatile market conditions:\n*   **Circuit Breaker:** Automatically detects API failures and pauses requests to prevent bans.\n*   **Bulkhead Pattern:** Isolates critical components so a failure in one module (e.g., price history) doesn't crash the trading engine.\n\n### ⚡ Scalable Architecture\n*   **Fully Asynchronous Engine:** Powered by the new `integrated_arbitrage_scanner`, capable of processing thousands of market updates per second without blocking.\n*   **Event-Driven Design:** Decoupled components communicate via an internal event bus for maximum flexibility.\n\n---\n\n## 📋 Project Overview\n\n| Metric               | Value                      |\n| -------------------- | -------------------------- |\n| **Architecture**     | Dual Brain (Logic + AI)    |\n| **Python**           | 3.11+                      |\n| **Testing**          | Comprehensive CI/CD        |\n| **License**          | MIT                        |\n\n## 🎯 Core Capabilities\n\n- **Multi-Game Arbitrage:** CS2, Dota 2, TF2, Rust.\n- **Advanced Target System:** Smart buy orders with auto-adjustment.\n- **Real-Time Monitoring:** WebSocket-based price tracking.\n- **AI-Powered:** Market sentiment analysis and self-healing capabilities.\n- **Secure:** Encrypted credentials and robust error handling.\n\n---\n\n## 🆕 Modular Skills (2026 Standard)\n\nThe project utilizes a modular skills architecture for rapid capability expansion:\n\n| Skill | Category | Description | Status |\n|-------|-----------|----------|--------|\n| **AI Arbitrage Predictor** | Data & AI | ML-based opportunity forecasting | ✅ Active |\n| **NLP Command Handler** | Interaction | Natural language control | ✅ Active |\n| **Portfolio Risk AI** | Finance | Deep portfolio analysis | ✅ Active |\n| **SkillsMP Integration** | DevOps | Seamless extension marketplace | ✅ Active |\n\n---\n\n## 🚀 Quick Start\n\n### 1. Environment Setup\n```bash\ngit clone https://github.com/Dykij/DMarket-Telegram-Bot.git\ncd DMarket-Telegram-Bot\npython -m venv .venv\nsource .venv/bin/activate  # Windows: .venv\\Scripts\\activate\npip install -r requirements.txt\n```\n\n### 2. Configuration\nCopy `.env.example` to `.env` and configure your API keys:\n```bash\ncp .env.example .env\n```\n*Required:* `TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN`, `DMARKET_PUBLIC_KEY`, `DMARKET_SECRET_KEY`.\n\n### 3. Launch\n```bash\npython -m src.main\n```\n\n---\n\n## 🤖 How to Contribute (AI Agents)\n\nThis repository is optimized for both human and AI contributions.\n\n1.  **Context Loading:** AI agents should first ingest `docs_archive/KNOWLEDGE_BASE.md` to understand architectural patterns and memory constraints.\n2.  **Code Standards:** All generated code must pass `flake8` linting and include type hints.\n3.  **Testing:** New features require corresponding `pytest` cases.\n4.  **Commits:** Use conventional commits (e.g., `feat:`, `fix:`, `chore:`).\n\nFor detailed protocols on inter-agent communication and memory updates, refer to the **Knowledge Base**.\n\n---\n\n## 🛠️ DevOps & Infrastructure\n\nThis repository adheres to modern 2026 standards:\n*   **CI/CD:** Automated testing and linting via GitHub Actions.\n*   **Docker:** Full containerization support.\n*   **Security:** Automated dependency scanning and secret detection.\n\n---\n\n## 🤝 Contributing (Humans)\n\nWe welcome contributions! Please follow the `CONTRIBUTING.md` guidelines.\n\n1.  Fork the repository.\n2.  Create a feature branch.\n3.  Commit your changes.\n4.  Push to the branch.\n5.  Open a Pull Request.\n\n---\n"},"thoughtSignature":""},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771168257978_382","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git add .github/ README.md && git commit -m \"Chore: GitHub Automation (Actions, Dependabot, GHCR)\" && git push origin dev"}}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":7431,"output":1487,"cacheRead":5380,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":8918,"cost":{"input":0.014861999999999998,"output":0.017844,"cacheRead":0.0010760000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.033782}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771168242124}}
