{"type":"message","id":"b800fd64","parentId":"65503fe4","timestamp":"2026-02-15T15:11:03.114Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"**Troubleshooting Command Execution**\n\nI'm currently dealing with a shell execution failure, likely due to PowerShell's incompatibility with `&&` command chaining, unlike bash. My immediate plan is to switch to sequential execution or utilize semicolons for command chaining. I'm leaning toward sequential execution to improve error detection.\n\n\n**Adapting Execution Strategy**\n\nI've decided to refine the approach. Instead of a direct switch to semicolons, I'm opting for a more controlled, sequential execution. This method offers superior error monitoring, enabling more precise troubleshooting. I'll also add a crucial check on the git status before proceeding.\n\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"exec_1771168263110_383","name":"exec","arguments":{"command":"git status"},"thoughtSignature":""}],"api":"google-vertex","provider":"google-vertex","model":"gemini-3-pro-preview","usage":{"input":9074,"output":107,"cacheRead":5648,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":9181,"cost":{"input":0.018147999999999997,"output":0.001284,"cacheRead":0.0011296000000000001,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0.0205616}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1771168258225}}
